page.title: 19Bramhope: Ecology (animals)
page.content: Many birds live in our area.The domesticated ones were a{budgie,hens, {geese}and a{pea-cock. The}most common birds observed were{blackbirds, {sparrows,lapwings,swallows}and {magpies.}Also seen were{blue-tits, {crows,curlews,great-tits,house {martins,jackdaws,kestrels,owls,pied {wagtails,pigeons,pheasants,robins, {rooks,sea-gulls,spotted woodpecker, {starlings,sky-larks,swifts,thrushes {and wrens.}On a lake these birds have been introduced;{black swans,swans, {Canada geese,grebes,mallards}and {coots.}Animals in fields were:{cows {(Freisans+Jerseys),sheep,horses,ponies {,goats}and{kids.Dogs}and{cats}were seen in gardens.There were single sightings of{frogs,tadpoles,rats}and {hares.Rabbits}and{squirrels}were in over half the area.Traces of{moles, {foxes}and{hedgehogs}were observed.
